Boil a #kettle{}.

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Meanwhile, heat a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{a drizzle}.

Once hot, add the @British pork mince{240%g} and @sliced mushrooms{180%g}.

Fry until the mince has browned and the mushrooms are cooked, ~{5-6%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

While the mince cooks, pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to a boil.

Add the @egg noodle nest{125%g} and cook until tender, ~{4%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and run under cold water to stop them sticking together.

When the mince has browned, drain and discard any excess fat. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Add the garlic and fry for ~{1%minute} more.

Add the @Szechuan paste{1%sachet}, @ketjap manis{50%g} and @soy sauce{25%ml}.

Simmer until thickened slightly, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir the cooked noodles into the sauce.

Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed.

Add a splash of water if the sauce is looking a little too thick.

Share your Szechuan pork noodles between your #serving bowls{}.

Enjoy!